We reiterated our previous year’s audit recommendations that Management:


(a) initiate immediate submission to the COA Auditor’s Office of all the unsubmitted disbursement vouchers and supporting documents pertaining to the current and years’ disbursements;

(b) instruct the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer, including all Accountable Officers to (i) strictly comply with the timely rendition of accounts and accountability reports so as not to delay the preparation of financial reports;

(ii) properly observe the due dates of submission of the required financial reports and supporting documents to the Audit Team; and

(c) set deadline for the submission of documents and pick up of checks, send demand letters to those officials and employees concerned, and impose sanctions against those who have continuously disregarded the set deadline for the submission of monthly accounts/reports to the Audit Team.

