We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to instruct the:

(a) Municipal Accountant to:

(i) analyze all the receivables and liabilities from/to GOCC, NGAs, LGUs, and NGOs/POs that are dormant, long outstanding and unsubstantiated for proper disposition and derecognition;

(ii) maintain supporting documents such as Memorandum of Agreement (MOA) / Trust Agreement (TA) to support the recorded balance of Due from/to GOCC, NGAs, LGUs, and NGOs/POs and ensure that the implementation of programs and projects identified therein will be properly monitored;

(iii) analyze and determine the details of the unutilized national government funds entrusted to the LGU;

(iv) reconcile with source agencies to ascertain the nature of the transferred funds, i.e.,  if the funds received require liquidation or are to be treated simply as subsidy to the LGU;

(v) if due for liquidation, prepare and submit liquidation reports for the expended portion and cause the return of excess funds to the source agencies; and

(vi) improve the safekeeping of important documents, particularly Memoranda of Agreement (MOA) and Trust Agreement (TA) for future reference; and

(b) Municipal Treasurer to exert best efforts to follow up from the Provincial Government the full liquidation of funds totaling to ₱553,099.06 for the construction of the public market which had long been completed.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to instruct the:

(a) Municipal Treasurer to

(i) demand payment of rental fees and security deposits from lessees who were delinquent as at year-end;



(ii) institute the civil remedies available pursuant to Section 174 of R.A. No. 7160; and



(iii) update and prepare, at least on a quarterly basis, the schedule of security deposits and delinquency reports and furnish copies to all departments/officers concerned for their perusal and monitoring;

(b) Municipal Accountant to

(i) record all security deposits received;



(ii) draw a Journal Entry Voucher (JEV) to reclassify the Guaranty/Security Deposits Payable account to Customers’ Deposits Payable account; and



