(c) Market Committee to

(i) enforce the cancellation of the lease contract/agreement of delinquent lessees and the revocation of their right to occupy the stalls;

(ii) execute a contract of lease with each stallholder signed by both parties for the full protection of the interest of the LGU;

(iii) administer properly the issuance of business permits to stallholders so that the latter could not operate their business unless there is an approved contract of lease and arrearages were fully settled;




(iv) review the reasonableness of the rental rates and update the Revenue Code, if warranted, taking into account the provisions of Section 130, R.A. No. 7160; and

(v) consider adopting the DBM Manual as guide in the efficient and effective operation of LEEs to ensure their viability in consonance with the Local Budget Circular No. 111 dated June 10, 2016.

